          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "9Be(18O,16C). A 16C secondary beam was produced from",
                " a 59.6-MeV/nucleon 18O primary beam impinging on a",
                " 4.5-mm thick 9Be target. The average beam intensity",
                " and the purity of 16C were up to about 1E4 particles",
                " per second and 90%, respectively. The beam energy was",
                " about 23.5 MeV/nucleon."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A 9.53 +- 0.12 mg/cm2 (CD2)n target was used to",
                " measure the inelastic scattering data.",
                "A 13.73 +- 0.13 mg/cm2 carbon target was employed",
                " to subtract the background coming from carbon atoms",
                " in the (CD2)n target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The time-of-flight provided by two plastic",
                " scintillator detectors and energy losses in a",
                " large-surface silicon detector were used to identify",
                " the second-beam."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PPAC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Three PPACs were installed upstream of targets",
                " to provide beam tracking information, with a",
                " resolution of the hit position on the target less",
                " than 1.0 mm."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SISD",
                "SI",
                "CSICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Several sets of telescopes were",
                " installed in a large vacuum chamber to detect and",
                " identify charged particles using a standard dE-E",
                " method. The telescope T0 and T2 were placed 156 and",
                " 157 mm away from the target to distinguish the carbon",
                " isotopes at forward angles and the recoil deuterons",
                " emitting to backward angles, respectively. The",
                " telescope T0 installed at around 0 degree is made up",
                " of three 1000-um-thick double sided silicon strip",
                " detectors, three 1500-um-thick SSDs, and a layer of",
                " 4-cm-thick CsI(Tl) crystals read out by photodiodes.",
                " The telescope T2, which consists of a 300-um-thick",
                " DSSD, a 1500-um-thick SSD, and a layer of CsI(Tl)",
                " crystals, was placed at ~69 degree relative to the",
                " beam direction. Each DSSD with an active area of",
                " 63.96 mm x 63.96 mm is divided into 32 strips on both",
                " sides. The angular coverage of the telescopes T0 and",
                " T2 are 0~12 degree and 57~82 degree, respectively.",
                " The overall angular resolution of the telescope T2",
                " was about 0.92 degree (FWHM)."
              ]
            }
          ],
